  <li>In a pan, place the oats, milk, vanilla extract, ground cinnamon and salt.</li>
  <li>Bring to boil and let it simmer until the porridge becomes thicker. This should take around 5 minutes unless you prefer the porridge runnier. Make sure you continuously stir so no lumps are formed.</li>
  <li>Pour into a bowl. For the topping, include the saturn peach or berries, sprinkle with cinnamon and honey. Spoon the yogurt if using it.</li>
  <li>Ready to be served.</li>
</ol>
